data.enText: to become an expert in a particular area of work, study or business; to spend more time on one area of work, etc. than on others

data.chText: 很多学生不愿过早地确定专业。
data.enText: Many students prefer not to specialize too soon.

data.chText: 这家商店专营手工制作的巧克力。
data.enText: The shop specializes in hand-made chocolates.

simple_means.memory_skill: special 特别的；专门的 + ize …化 → 专门化；专攻

tr: evolve so as to lead to a new species or develop in a way most suited to the environment
become more focus on an area of activity or field of study
example: She specializes in Near Eastern history
this kind of beak has become specialized in certain Galapagos finches
Could you please specify your criticism of my paper?

tr: devote oneself to a special area of work
example: This baker specializes in French bread

value.boxr_value: in BRIT, also use 英国英语亦用 specialise

value.def: If you specialize in a thing, you know a lot about it and concentrate a great deal of your time and energy on it, especially in your work or when you are studying or training. You also use specialize to talk about a restaurant which concentrates on a particular type of food.

example.ex: ...a University professor who specializes in the history of the Russian empire.
example.tran: 专门研究俄罗斯帝国历史的大学教授

example.ex: ...a Portuguese restaurant which specializes in seafood.
example.tran: 主打海味的葡萄牙餐馆

value.tran: 专门从事;专门经营;专门研究;专攻

example.ex: This degree offers a major specialisation in Social Policy alongside a course in Sociology.
example.tran: 该学位主修社会政策，同时也包括一门社会学课程。

example.ex: ...an economist who has avoided narrow specialization.
example.tran: 避免了专业范围过窄的经济学家

rootsaffixes.indicate: = look, kind, sort 外观；种类
rootsaffixes.title: spec(i)

partsOfSpeech.dec: con 共同 + spec 外观；种类 + ific 使…的 → 同种的
spec 外观；种类 + ial …的 →〔属于〕某种类 → 特别的
special 特别的；专门的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 特点；特产
special 特别的；专门的 + ize …化 → 专门化；专攻
speci 外观；种类 + es → 种类，物种
spec 外观；种类 + ific 产生…的 → 分门别类的 → 具体的
spec 外观；种类 + ification …化 → 具体说明
speci 外观；种类 + men 表实物名词 → 作为某一种类的样品 → 标本
speci 外观；种类 + ous …的 → 外观相似，而实质不是 → 似是而非的
